race.comment: HUSTLE IN HEELS (7) resumes for her second campaign. She was a very smart winner on debut here over 1200m, tackling a pair of good 3yo races after that when hard in the market. She's been jumping out well, the only niggle is the 955m trip. DEMARCATE (9) is another resuming for their second preparation. He's a sharp 3yo who didn't quite measure up to some classy 2yo form last time in but showed ability nonetheless. He maps well now with the Hayes yard. FUROSSHI (6) was a narrow winner when last seen at Seymour over 1000m, tough when covering ground. She's racing consistently well and should be in the finish again. OCTRAIN (2) was solid fresh at Sale and maps for the suck run here. His best form is good enough. MANHATTAN THUNDER (4) comes through the same race at Sale and is in the mix.
